  "prompt": "How does one choose the best global health insurance plans for frequent travelers or expatriates?",
  "response": "Here are key considerations for choosing the best global health insurance plans:\n\n1. Coverage Factors\n- Comprehensive international medical coverage\n- Emergency evacuation services\n- Direct billing with global hospitals\n- Coverage in multiple countries\n- No geographical restrictions\n\n2. Plan Considerations\n- Flexible/worldwide coverage options\n- High maximum benefit limits\n- Low deductibles\n- Transparent claim processes\n- Option for routine and preventive care\n\n3. Cost Evaluation\n- Premium pricing\n- Out-of-pocket expenses\n- Co-payment structures\n- Annual vs. monthly payment options\n\n4. Specific Traveler Needs\n- Frequency of international travel\n- Duration of stays abroad\n- Personal health conditions\n- Age and risk profile\n- Specific destination risks\n\n5. Recommended Providers\n- Cigna Global\n- Allianz Care\n- IMG Global\n- GeoBlue\n- William Russell\n\n6. Additional Recommended Checks\n- Customer service responsiveness\n- Claims processing efficiency\n- Network of international healthcare providers\n- COVID-19 coverage\n- Repatriation services\n\n7. Personal Research\n- Compare multiple quotes\n- Read detailed policy documents\n- Check customer reviews\n- Consult insurance brokers specializing in international coverage",
